Annotation.note:
Let $ABCD$ be a trapezoid with base $AB$ satisfying $AC=BC$. Denote the
midpoint of $AB$ by $H$. Consider a line $g$ through $H$. Denote further the
intersection points of $g$ with $AD$, $BD$, resp. by $P$, $Q$. Then the angles
$ACP$ and $QCB$ are equal.
